e a Legends only item but dropped for about 2 weeks on this server. I also have a Coldain Military Wristguard a quest item that few people have that now has the focus effect of Extended Affliction III.  This makes root/dot method must more efficient for groups or soloing.  Your FR and AC/atk debuffs will last longer on raids and pvp as well. He also has 2 instaclick buffs.  My stats self buffed are:<br><br>HP: 2303<br>AC: 935ish<br>DR: 142<br>PR: 151<br>MR:164<br>FR: 202<br>CR: 212<br>Mana:3235 (as seen on magelo)<br>Mana regen: 10 per tic standing between PotG/C,Mask of Hunter, MC1<br><br>My AA skills are: <br><br>-Runspeed 3: jboot speed<br><br>-Natural regen 3: 3 additional regeneration points.<br><br>-Spell Casting Fury2. I get 1916 crits on Moonfire 1716 crits on Wildfire without mage dmg focus items.  In PvP that equates to over 1k dmg in a single nuke.  Very deadly.  Also leads to faster quad kiting for easier leveling.<br><br>-Spell Casting Mastery1: Less cost on spells and less chance on fizzles.  Very useful all around<br><br>-Healing Gift: Chance to critical on heals for double the normal amount. Thats a heal of 1956ish on Natures Touch and 770 on the 3 sec casting Chloroblast.  <br><br>-Mental clarity1: 1 more point of mana regen to even it out at 10 mana/tic regen standing <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->                 <br><br>1 AA unspent<br><br>I have basically every spell a druid can get. <br>-PotG<br>-PotC: quested single target version of potg<br>-Natures Recovery: 1.5 min regen for a heal of 1000hp. <br>-Moonfire: best druid nuke that drops<br>-Mask of the hunter: rare druid see invis/mana regen<br>-Legacy of thorn: group DS<br>-Regrowth of the Grove: group regrowth (RARE)<br>-Circle of Seasons<br>-Remove Curse<br><br>Thats pretty much every droppable spell a druid can get outside of Ancient spells which no longer drop.<br><br>As a druid you are incredibly vital on a pvp server.  You are a high speed pvp machine with the ability to heal yourself or your groupmates and buff them up a great amount.  On raids your fast heals keep the main tank alive while CHs are incoming and the shamans are busy slowing or torporing people.  Your buffs are important to keeping exp and raid groups alive.  With NR and rotg you dont even need to heal exp group tanks and the regen off the two is vital for pulling on raids.<br><br>I also have a 51 barbarian fairly stripped down shaman on Vallon Zek who had a good reputation along with a lvl 23 jbooted ranger with good weapons and resist gear to pk with on the same account.  The Shaman is 2 steps away from epic (CoM and Hole) and has sow boots.<br><br>Email me at Jester@nycap.rr.com for offers for this account.  The combination of this incredibly uber druid along with 2 other characters on VZ, which is a completely different political setup than TZ, is not offered very often.  I only want offers that are worthy of this account.<br><br>-Aare<br><br><br>EDIT:  **SOLD**<br><br><br><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub77.ezboard.com/uaaredormistwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aaredor Mistwalker</A> at: 6/26/02 2:49:35 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub77.ezboard.com/uxganja.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xganja</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(6/23/02 9:21:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub77.ezboard.com/ftallonzektimes4735frm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=111.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aaredor: 60 Druid 19 AA points. 51 Shm stripped,Jboot tw</span><hr size=1> doesnt that lodi shield belong to guild? im sure someone in guild can use that<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgco